parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, resulting in extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
brakes fade away
extended stopping distance
pumping the brakes restores functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads and rotors can cause reduced braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads and rotors show excessive wear
grinding or screeching noise when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rear wheel cylinder can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
rear brake issues
rebuilding of rear wheel cylinders necessary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the front disc caliper can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
front brake issues
rebuilding of front disc caliper necessary.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Shimmy and Steering Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end shimmy can cause loss of vehicle control, especially when driving over bumps, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shimmies or vibrates while driving at various speeds
especially when driving over bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause injuries, fatalities, and property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire after a crash or accident
potentially causing harm to occupants and bystanders.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable bracket can cause the throttle cable to pop out, resulting in a loss of power and unintended idle speed, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The throttle cable pops out of the plastic bracket
the vehicle idles or loses power
sudden drop to fast idle speed
loss of acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle failure can cause an immediate drop to fast idle speed, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Sudden drop to fast idle speed
loss of power or acceleration
unintended idle speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion.
symptoms: The ignition switch is difficult to turn
the ignition switch sticks in the start or accessory position
accessories fail to function when the switch is stuck in the accessory position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A short circuit in the wiring harness can cause a fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
there are signs of burning or melting on the wiring harness
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.
